headline: Trump Trade: President says first deal on tariffs ‘close’ as China ups duties
summary: Catch up on the top industries and stocks that were impacted, or were predicted to be impacted, by the comments, actions and policies of President Donald Trump with this daily recap compiled by The Fly: CHINA RAISES TARIFFS: China raised its tariffs on U.S. goods to 125% from 84%. “If the U.S. continues to impose tariffs on Chinese goods exported to the U.S., China will ignore it,” the government said in a statement.
